- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also likely as the paper uses reinforcement learning to guide the language model towards a specific goal. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is relevant as the paper uses backpropagation to update the language model. 
- cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is relevant as the paper uses a pre-trained neural language model. 
- cs.SD (Sound) is less likely as the paper does not deal with sound or audio data.
